column2: Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Water is calm- very clear sky- some algae bloom (possibly due to very windy days on the 3rd and 4th of October).
Ice was off turtle lake on Monday- April 28- 1994.  We have seen 3 loons on the lake!
Also took a reading at 6: 30 pm.  Windy at 2pm - less windy (not calm) at 6: 30 pm. secchi readings 5' both times.
Sunny - water was calm - no wind.
Sunny- clear day- calm wind.  Lake water calm.  What is happening to our lake   we used to get 10' clarity.

Lake level up some after rain.  Sample taken by pat Carroll who was with me + Department of Natural Resources for training.  He could not believe my readings were so poor.  He checked several areas of lake and said he had to strain to get 4'!!
Lake water temperature is down from last week 76 degrees- windy day- clear skies.
Time was late for a sample but lake was very calm. it was overcast + raining lightly but we got a good reading.
Overcast-calm day after many rain storms.
Sunny day--this is the best reading we have gotten!!!  took it 3x to be sure!
Sunny- very calm day.  Summer had a lot of rain and more plant growth.  Green scum has finally sunk to the bottom and disappeared.  Top sample- no depth reported- assumed 1'.
Taken after rain and wind storm.
No rain for several days-water calm + getting more plants floating!
Calm- overcast- thin layer of ice on lake twice but has melted- chemical samples taken today.
A lot of holiday boat traffic.
Very few boats on lake this weekend even though weather is warm + beautiful.
Water sample taken after 2 days of high winds.
Last water sample before ice - very warm weather!
All days so far this season were clear (5/25-6/23).  Very much rain this spring.  Marsh water high.
Ice out April 5 and two migrant loons on our lake.
Lake unexpectedly clear after five days of rain.  Today is partly cloudy and calm.
Beautiful- calm- sunny day but after week of rain and wind.  We still have a loon.
Sample taken after day of high wind and rain.
Very calm- clear and many days no rain.
Partly cloudy- mild wind.  Still no rain.
Clear sky- mild wind.  No rain for many days.
Very calm and sunny after a big thunderstorm last night.  First rain in many days.
After very hot weather and first rain in about 20-30 days.
A very hot summer- little rain- lake is low but water is clear.
Water clear after a few days of wind and rain.  Lake still lower than it should be.
Loons arrive 3/28/2003 - Gone first week in May.
Clear day- no wind- water calm.
After a week of rain.  Lake level up about 3 inches!
Lake low- calm- no rain- water clear.
Lake low- calm- no rain.  Water clear.
Beautiful day.  Brooke Robinson and Rachel from DNR were in the boat with us.  Water and skies clear.
Last sample this fall.  Very clear fall day.  Mild wind.
after many inches of rain over weekend
Lake is higher than last 2-3 years
after 3 weeks of rain- water is murky and cooler then usual-down about 5-6" since 6/1/04
Lake is very low - Brooke Robinson here for zebra mussel testing.
Sunny- calm day - only with a little boat traffic this weekend.
Little rain - water still running out of lake at Turtle Lake Road - Brooke Robinson here to test zebra mussels.
Lake very low all summer due to drought and leak in marsh emptying Turtle Creek.
hot weather- hot nights- water level rapidly going down
Lake has had a lot of algae.
Aquatic plant life is very tall this year.
Strong winds in June.  Received new thermometer and have better temperature readings.
Lake has been slow to clear up but we are finally getting more than 10 ft of clarity.
A very cold- wet windy spring
Very much rain and water churned up - learned correct way to read water color!!
Changed recording method to D.O. meter/
Out in boat with Audrey Green and Mary Knipper for Zebra Mussel Testing.
Discovered zebra mussels for the first time.
water murky after 4th of July boat traffic- four white egrets on lake
quiet day- partly cloudy- NW wind-- after week of very hight temps.
no rain for several days- water is warm
water clear- 2 white egrets still on lake
ice out eary - March 13th. Very warm weather in March
lake is very clear this time of year. After warm March - now cool
dry june- sporadic heavy shifting winds
summer of high heat and no rain
hot and dry June and July- very low water. Very little color in water
water down about 1 1/2 ft. and getting lower
a cool day and the lowest ever lake in over 30 years
boats are out - lake now has zebra mussels - lowest consistent readings in years
Very cold spring and much rain. Very few piers or boats in. This sample is late.
Our lake is loosing water; dam not working but breech in creek causing loss of much water
Two days of big storms; lake is high but going down fast
Sunny but windy Lake is high from all the rain
Lake went down 2" over the week. Wish we could get help fixing the breach in the creek.
First time went with Gronerts- a little wary.
Lake very clear this year. Warm weather. Secchi reading taken from kayak. Four of us took a 3 mi kayak ride around the lake--on October 2!
Boat in first time yesterday; calm ; clear; sunny
a lot of possible blue-green algae present
possible blue-green algae covering plants in "plant ring" around lake
Clumps of algae on water surface near shore; floating plants near shore.

column1: Data collectors Mark + Kim Alba (not Brad Baas- Mary Baas).  System would not allow change.

column2: Some algae near shore; heron cruising; egret fishing. Slightly overcast; SE winds light and variable.
Partly cloudy with light breeze. No algae.  Assisted by Beth Auer.
No wake lifted after having been in place for approximately 1 1/2 weeks due to extreme rainfall amounts.
Calm- clear; green algae on shoreline
Large algae covering at shoreline- especially in channel.  Underwater aquatic plants coated with algae.  Very large bass seen swimming through shallow water near north shore.

Pontoon session with Grayson and Irene (youth)- Beth Auer- and Mary Baas.  67 degrees; sunny + clear w/slight breeze.  Much algae around edges of channel.  Strong aquatic plant growth throughout lake.  Observed Fish (northern +) in channel- blue heron- green heron- painted turtle.
Clear color- clear water- calm and sunny.  Perfect day.
Very clear- clear water- calm and sunny.  Beautiful day.
Greenish- flaky algae- wavy- scum but swimmable.
Some black floating blobs (typical August)- suspended algae throughout water column- still and a bit stagnant.
Greenish- yellow- calm- swimmable and a beautiful day.
Heavy rainfall previous day. Water clear- despite low secchi reading. Very heavy boat traffic on lake this summer. Many turtles.
Few fish in shallow water. Light breeze. Bald eagles (2) overhead.
clear- calm- lake temp 78 degrees F
clear- calm- no clouds- beautiful- lake temp 78 degrees F
clear- calm- sunny- lake temperature 74 degrees F
clear- calm- sunny w/no clouds- air temp 77 degrees F; lake temp 76 degrees F
Calm + quiet. Some black blobs on surface - typical late August. Several small turtles floating just below surface at 6 ft depth and middle of lake (spiny softshell).
